            <p><h2 style="color:black; text-align:left"> <b>What is the cost of a trip to Ecuador?</b></h2></p>
            <p>
                Ecuador does not have its own currency like other countries in
                South America, but uses the US Dollar. However, it is not a very
                expensive country in which to travel.
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify;"> <h4 style="color:black" id="cruisesFiltersDesktop"> <b>Ecuador</b></h4></p>
            <p>
                It is one of the countries in the Latin America region with the
                greatest tourist offer, so you can find basic options at reduced
                prices, as well as luxury options for accommodation and meals.
            </p>
            <p style="text-align:justify;"> <h4 style="color:black" id="cruisesFiltersDesktop"> <b>Galapagos</b></h4></p>
            <p>
                The most important expense when we take a tour in a country is
                transportation: flights between cities, hours in a train, long
                bus connections to reach nature destinations, etc. All of these
                options are one of the main expenses during your trip, both in
                time and money. Ecuador is a small country, where most of the
                tourist attractions are within a few hours of each other. Therefore,
                <b>transport costs are not going to be an issue</b> when exploring the
                entire country and its different ecosystems and cultures.
            </p>
            <p><h3 style="color:#398AC9;text-align:left"><b>Average Daily Costs</b></h3></p>
            <p>
                <b>Budget: Less than $60</b>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px">
                        <span>Budget guesthouses: $8–20 per person</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px">
                        <span>Set lunches: $3–5</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px">
                        <span>Bike rental or cheap activities: $10 - $25</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px">
                        <span>Bus transportation: $5 - $10</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>Midrange: $80–250</b>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px">
                        <span>Room for two in a  midrange hotel: $60–120</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px">
                        <span>Meal and dinner for two in a restaurant: $40–70</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px">
                        <span>Group tours: $45–90 per person</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px">
                        <span>Jungle lodges: from $80 per day per person.</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
                <b>Top end: More than $300</b>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ul>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px">
                        <span>Top Amazon lodges: around $400 per day per person</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px" id="consideration">
                        <span>Exclusive Private Activities: from $75 per person</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px">
                        <span>Double Room in a Luxury Colonial Hotel or Hacienda: from $140</span>
                    </li>
                    <li type="disc" style="margin-left:16px; margin-top:10px">
                        <span>Meal and dinner for two in a high-end restauant: $120 - $180</span>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <p><h2 style="color:black; text-align:left"> <b>The cost of travel in Ecuador depends on a variety of factors</b></h2></p>
            <p><h3 style="color:#398AC9;text-align:left"><b>Seasonality</b></h3></p>
            <p>
                Ecuador has high and low seasons and prices can vary accordingly.
            </p>
            <p>
                The high tourist season in Ecuador runs from mid-June to early September
                and starts again in late December. These high seasons are more about when
                people are able to take vacations rather than the weather.
            </p>
